description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB TITLE: Speech &amp; Language Therapist.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPARTMENT: Adult Learning Disability Community Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOCATION: South Hub&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND AND SALARY: Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week Monday to Friday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Speech and Language Therapist to join the South Hub Learning Disability team within Lincolnshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic, creative and flexible Speech and Language Therapist who is passionate about working with people with learning disabilities. You will join a supportive and friendly team of Speech and Language Therapists, Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Psychologists, Psychiatrists and Nurses to ensure the delivery of a high quality, holistic service to people with learning disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for providing specialist speech and language assessment and therapy to individuals and contributing to the overall team assessment, formulation and treatment for individual service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent line management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical supervision including peer supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong commitment to your CPD needs and support towards further training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Links with other Speech and Language Therapy teams and Adult Learning Disability CEN within the local area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility over working hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity to develop your skills and knowledge in a supportive and friendly environment. This would be an ideal post for someone looking for a rewarding position in a friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Depending on the suitability of the candidate, the team would consider a Band 5 Speech and Language Therapist who wishes to progress to becoming a Band 6.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must be registered with the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC), and the RCSLT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this post or arrange please contact Mary Sheehan, Speech and Language Therapist on mary.sheehan@LPFT.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
